text.__SUMMARY__: Eulimastoma canaliculatum is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Distribution:
This species occurs in the following locations:
Aruba
Bonaire
Caribbean Sea
Colombia
Curaçao
Gulf of Mexico
Jamaica
Mexico
Puerto Rico
